Title: Effect of hydration on the anatomical form of human dry skulls
Leukocyte telomere length in children born following blastocyst-stage embryo transfer
Summary: Analyses of whole-genome sequencing data in children and validation in mouse models show that offspring born from blastocyst-stage embryo transfer have shorter leukocyte telomere lengths.

Title: Viral load dynamics of SARS-CoV-2 Delta and Omicron variants following multiple vaccine doses and previous infection
Summary: COVID vaccination can reduce virus levels in breakthrough infections, which in turn may reduce transmission of the virus. By using qRT-PCR cycle threshold as a surrogate of virus levels, the authors here show that this positive effect of vaccination wanes relatively quickly for Omicron breakthrough infection.

Title: Novel method to delineate palatal rugae and assess their complexity using fractal analysis
The care cascade following a supportive management intervention for patients presenting to a radiation oncology clinic
Association between medication adherence to chronic diseases and shift-work schedules in the Korean working population
Novice-performed point-of-care ultrasound for home-based imaging
Effect of remdesivir post hospitalization for COVID-19 infection from the randomized SOLIDARITY Finland trial
Summary: Many survivors of COVID-19 experience persistent symptoms, continuing beyond three months from the onset of infection. In this study, authors investigate the effect of remdesivir on recovery and long-COVID-19 symptoms, as well as quality of life and other symptom outcomes, in the 1-year follow-up of a randomised trial.

Title: Real world outcomes of photodynamic therapy for chronic central serous chorioretinopathy
Efficacy of supermarket and web-based interventions for improving dietary quality: a randomized, controlled trial
Summary: In a randomized control trial, individuals who received dietitian-led counseling in the supermarket, together with web-based tools, had improved dietary quality in comparison to a control group, as assessed by adherence to the heart-healthy DASH diet plan.
